                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6661: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-16T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 16, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>263. Your 299, November 12, 5 p.m. In view of the Greek Government’s statement, a
                    proclamation declaring the neutrality of the <pb facs="0574" n="562"
                        xml:id="pg_562"/> United States in the war between Greece and Italy<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d459fn50">Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, November 16, 1940, p. 426.</note> is being issued today. If
                    you consider it desirable you may inform the Greek Government that this action
                    has followed the official confirmation by Greece of the state of war, and that
                    similar action has been taken in respect to the other belligerents as they have
                    become involved. You may state that the proclamation is to be construed in no
                    way as being an indication of any lessening of the sympathy of this Government
                    for Greece in its present conflict with Italy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
